                <h2>About Nainital</h2>
                <p>Nainital is a picturesque hill station nestled around the pristine Naini Lake in Uttarakhand, India. Known for its colonial-era charm reflected in Victorian-style architecture and scenic views of surrounding hills, it offers boating on the lake, panoramic viewpoints like Snow View Point, and a bustling Mall Road lined with shops and eateries. A popular destination year-round, Nainital combines natural beauty with cultural allure, making it a delightful retreat in the Himalayan foothills.</p>
            </div> 
